    ],
    "lyrics": {
      "text": "What shall__ we now call___ you, O Saints of God? Ho-ly Cher-u-bim, for__ Christ doth rest up--on you at all times.__ Six-wing’d Ser-a-phim, in that___ ye glo-ri--fied Him with-out cease.__ Pure An-----gels, for ye showed your__ bod-ies__ nought but scorn;__ and Pow-----ers, for ye work__ through__ won-drous mir-a-cles.__ Your names are di----vers and__ man-i--fold,__ but great--er still____ are your__ gifts of__ grace.__ O in---ter----cede__ with the Sav--iour that our souls____ be____ saved."
    }
  }
}